# Styling Conventions

## Single CSS file
- All styles live in `src/App.css` — no CSS modules, no separate files
- Organize with section headers: `/* ───── ComponentName ───── */`

## CSS custom properties
- Never hardcode colors — always use `var(--property-name)`
- `--accent` is set dynamically per subject; use it for all interactive elements
- `--bg-primary`, `--bg-secondary`, `--bg-elevated` for backgrounds
- `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary` for text
- `--border`, `--border-strong` for dividers

## Theme
- Dark mode only (no light/dark toggle in UI)
- All colors defined in `:root` block
- `ThemeProvider` context still exists but only applies dark class

## Responsive breakpoints
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) { /* Tablet: sidebar collapses */ }
@media (max-width: 520px) { /* Phone: stack everything vertically */ }
```

## Layout patterns
- Sidebar + content: CSS Grid (`grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr`)
- Card grids: Flexbox with `flex-wrap: wrap`
- Content max-width: `780px` centered
- Spacing: use multiples of 4px (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48)

## Mermaid diagrams
- Container has `overflow-x: auto` for mobile scrolling
- Max width on desktop; no max on mobile
- Captions use `--text-secondary` color

## Interactive elements
- Buttons: `background: var(--accent)`, `border-radius: var(--radius-sm)`
- Hover states: `var(--accent-hover)` or `var(--bg-hover)`
- Focus states: visible outline using accent color
- Transitions: `0.15s ease` for color changes, `0.2s ease` for transforms
